"I don't appreciate this idea either, if a number of people take a stand on the same issue, then some are more likely to disregard it as a so-called collective effort and not be recognized as a large group of concerned citizens."
What the governor’s employees called a “concentrated spam attack,” others would probably call “advocacy.”
The Facebook era makes it easy to crop a message by simply blocking a critic or deleting a negative comment.
It is much cleaner than in the past if you had done the same thing that employees were sent out to collect and burn newspapers with critical editorials or to arrest and silence protesters.
But that is exactly what is happening digitally.
Hogan isn’t the first public official to be criticized for flouting Facebook and other social media.
